headline: Assessing Nike Shares After Job Cuts and Five Year Drop of Over 40%
summary: If you’ve been watching NIKE’s stock lately, you’re probably asking yourself whether now is the right time to make a move. At a last close of $69.31, the stock has seen some dramatic shifts. It is down 2.2% over the past week and has fallen 11.2% for the month. Over a longer view, returns are even softer, with the stock slipping 20.8% in the last year and experiencing a 41.5% drop over the past five years.
